Nothing.

21:37.505 --> 21:39.996
- It's getting worse.
- I don't know what to tell you.

21:40.174 --> 21:41.789
- What are you looking for?
- ( touch-tones beeping )

21:41.967 --> 21:43.252
Hey, just give me a second.

21:43.427 --> 21:44.963
( all chanting )
Hell, no! We won't go!

21:45.137 --> 21:47.173
Hell, no!
We won't go!

21:47.348 --> 21:49.964
( phone rings)

21:50.142 --> 21:51.382
Mom! Mom!

21:51.560 --> 21:52.720
Travis:
Where the hell are you?

21:52.895 --> 21:54.510
Dad, why do you
have Mom's phone?

21:54.688 --> 21:55.768
I'm with your mother.

21:55.940 --> 21:57.476
We're coming to get you.
Tell us where you are.

21:57.650 --> 21:59.857
There's a protest.
I'm at a protest.

22:00.027 --> 22:01.358
- A protest?
- Where is he?

22:01.529 --> 22:03.065
- Where?
- The cops,

22:03.239 --> 22:04.649
they shot some
homeless man, Dad.

22:04.824 --> 22:06.439
This poor guy,
he wasn't doing anything.

22:06.617 --> 22:08.153
Okay, let us
come and get you.

22:08.327 --> 22:11.034
The people were taking action.
This is important, Dad!

22:11.205 --> 22:13.116
Yeah, I get it.
| get it. Okay, but--

22:13.290 --> 22:14.541
Dad, I'm part of it, okay?

22:14.708 --> 22:16.289
I gotta go.
I gotta go, Dad.

22:16.460 --> 22:17.666
Chris--

22:17.837 --> 22:19.873
( chanting continues)

22:21.298 --> 22:22.799
I know where he is.

22:24.510 --> 22:27.217
Cafeteria food's designed
to survive a nuclear strike.

22:27.388 --> 22:30.551
Expires in, like, the year 3000.

22:30.724 --> 22:31.884
What did you come back for?

22:32.059 --> 22:34.641
Uh, Nick, my son,
is not feeling well.

22:34.812 --> 22:36.348
Well, that's smart.

22:36.522 --> 22:38.979
LAPD lockup,
they have pharmaceuticals.

22:39.149 --> 22:41.731
Nick was here
when l was a freshman.

22:41.902 --> 22:43.517
He seemed nice.

22:43.696 --> 22:45.812
Yeah, he's a good kid.

22:45.990 --> 22:47.480
Yeah.

22:47.658 --> 22:50.570
Uh, the looters
hit pharmacies first,

22:50.744 --> 22:54.077
then gun shops,
liquor stores.

22:54.248 --> 22:56.990
The less you go out,
the less chance you get exposed.

22:59.086 --> 23:00.872
(Tobias grunts)

23:05.676 --> 23:08.383
Hey, Miss C, have you
seen any of 'em yet?

23:08.554 --> 23:11.261
I mean, I've only
seen 'em online.

23:11.432 --> 23:13.548
No.
Let's hurry this up.

23:17.605 --> 23:19.186
Mother lode.

23:25.446 --> 23:26.856
Wow, you're stocking up
for a while.

23:27.031 --> 23:29.568
It's gonna be a while.

23:29.742 --> 23:31.949
So your mom's back, then?

23:32.119 --> 23:34.201
My uncle's been around.

23:34.371 --> 23:36.453
You should stock up,
too, Miss C.

23:37.958 --> 23:40.074
No, we have food.

23:44.757 --> 23:47.624
(scrubbing )

23:53.474 --> 23:56.090
I'm sorry.

23:56.268 --> 23:59.476
She should have been
back by now.

23:59.647 --> 24:01.308
Yeah, I know.

24:01.482 --> 24:04.599
Someone should
have called...

24:04.777 --> 24:06.233
by now.

24:13.619 --> 24:15.280
Thank you.

24:17.665 --> 24:19.405
(sighs)

24:22.795 --> 24:26.913
Mr. and Mrs. Cruz:
J‘ Happy birthday to you... J‘

24:27.091 --> 24:30.458
- I hate you.
- J‘ Happy birthday to you... J‘

24:30.636 --> 24:32.001
I know.

24:32.179 --> 24:38.015
J‘ Happy birthday,
dear Gladys J‘

24:38.185 --> 24:43.020
- J‘ Happy birthday to you. J‘
- ( sirens wailing)

24:43.190 --> 24:45.272
( cans rattling )

24:49.446 --> 24:50.697
Tobias:
The desert will be safer

24:50.864 --> 24:52.445
because things
will fall apart now.

24:52.616 --> 24:56.200
No satellites, no Internet,
no cell phones.

24:56.370 --> 24:58.577
Communications will fail
'cause no one's there

24:58.747 --> 24:59.862
to manage the servers.

25:00.040 --> 25:02.827
The electrical grid will
collapse for the same reason.

25:03.002 --> 25:04.993
It's all gonna go to hell.

25:05.170 --> 25:06.501
And that's what they don't get.

25:06.672 --> 25:08.879
When civilization ends,
it ends fast.

25:09.049 --> 25:10.710
They're gonna contain it.

25:10.884 --> 25:12.875
The same "they"
that's supposed to warn us?

25:14.388 --> 25:17.630
- Come on.
- ( distant rustling )

25:17.808 --> 25:19.514
(groaning)

25:19.685 --> 25:21.141
No, wait-- Miss C.

25:24.648 --> 25:28.687
( groaning on speakers)

25:29.695 --> 25:32.061
(groaning continues)

25:33.741 --> 25:35.072
It's one of them.

25:35.242 --> 25:38.154
( static crackling )

25:38.328 --> 25:40.705
(groaning continues)

25:44.501 --> 25:46.492
( distant alarm beeping )

25:46.670 --> 25:49.582
Let's go. Let's go.
Go, go, go, go.

25:49.757 --> 25:52.248
- Let's go.
-( beeping continues)

25:52.426 --> 25:54.508
Let's go. Go.

25:59.266 --> 26:01.427
Oh, God.

26:01.602 --> 26:03.092
Leaveit

26:03.270 --> 26:05.181
Tobias, leave it.

26:10.027 --> 26:11.563
Oh, God.

26:11.737 --> 26:13.602
Okay, get the door.

26:13.781 --> 26:15.271
Okay.

26:15.449 --> 26:17.940
Oh, God.

26:18.118 --> 26:20.109
Artie?

26:28.629 --> 26:30.540
Artie.

26:34.301 --> 26:37.464
-( raspy breathing )
- We-- we gotta go. We gotta go.

26:39.723 --> 26:41.099
(door rattling )

26:44.228 --> 26:45.843
Artie, can you hear me?

26:46.021 --> 26:47.636
He can't hear you.
You know he can't.

26:49.817 --> 26:51.978
We'll get you help, Artie.

27:00.452 --> 27:02.158
Artie, stop.

27:02.329 --> 27:04.615
We're gonna get you help, okay?
We'll get you--

27:04.790 --> 27:06.075
Tobias:
No, no.

27:06.250 --> 27:08.662
- No, stop!
- Tobias: No, no!

27:16.176 --> 27:17.586
Madison:
No, Tobias!

27:17.761 --> 27:20.173
- No, no, no, no! Ah!
- No! Tobias!

27:21.807 --> 27:23.672
Oh, no, no, no!

27:23.851 --> 27:24.931
(screaming )

27:25.102 --> 27:27.309
(grunting)

27:27.479 --> 27:29.435
Help me!

27:38.323 --> 27:39.938
Oh, no.
No, no!

27:41.869 --> 27:43.154
(grunting)

27:48.500 --> 27:51.207
- ( grunting)
- ( squelching)

27:51.378 --> 27:53.460
( panting )

28:28.832 --> 28:30.072
(engine starts)

28:30.250 --> 28:32.036
( crowd shouting )

28:34.254 --> 28:37.337
(Travis, echoing)
Chris!

28:37.507 --> 28:39.088
( crowd shouting )

28:39.259 --> 28:43.377
- Chris!
- Chris!

28:43.555 --> 28:46.547
( distorted voices )

28:46.725 --> 28:49.182
Chris!

28:55.609 --> 28:57.941
Liza:
Christopher James Manawa!

28:59.279 --> 29:01.361
- Christopher James Manawa.
- We gotta go, man.

29:01.531 --> 29:02.737
Dad, he was unarmed,
but they shot him.

29:02.908 --> 29:04.864
No, they shot him
like a dozen times.

29:05.035 --> 29:06.775
- Tell us on the way.
- I'm doing what you taught me.

29:06.954 --> 29:09.195
This is what you taught me.
Dad, we stand up for people.

29:09.373 --> 29:11.238
Travis: I know, I know, but
there's a time and a place--

29:11.416 --> 29:12.826
Chris: Right now.
This is happening right now.

29:13.001 --> 29:14.457
( conversation continues
indistinctly )

29:14.628 --> 29:17.119
(sirens wailing,
horn honking )

29:17.297 --> 29:18.457
Travis:
Liza!

29:18.632 --> 29:20.463
Enough.
( continues indistinctly )

29:20.634 --> 29:22.465
- Okay, we gotta go.
- This is important.

29:22.636 --> 29:24.376
Come on, man.
You're important, okay?

29:24.554 --> 29:25.634
Christopher,
listen to your father.

29:25.806 --> 29:28.889
( police radio chatter)

29:29.059 --> 29:30.720
